heisigStory: This odd but common kanji is built up of the character for not yet into which a pair of animal horns has been inserted.
koohiiStory1: You horny bastard, don´t come, at least not yet!
koohiiStory2: Here I see, of all things, Bambi. His animal horns have not yet come out. (As we can see in the kanji, the animal horns are not at the top, not "poking through". ) Remember: Bambi will soon come to have a great set of animal horns but they have not yet come out.
